    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test condition and that the E/uval metric for all three QoIs is well below the 1.96 threshold, providing sufficient confidence that the FEA framework adequately predicts compression-bending performance for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the defined COU. Overall credibility is assessed as sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device application.",
